<item>
            <title>[LU-20011] lfs mirror: Invalid layout: Incomplete mirror - must go to EOF</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-20011</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If a file with a partial PFL layout (i.e. no &lt;tt&gt;EOF&lt;/tt&gt; component) has a mirror added with &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs mirror extend&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; it is then impossible to remove the mirror, add a new EOF component, or &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs mirror split&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to return to the original state, receiving the error &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs mirror: Invalid layout: Incomplete mirror - must go to EOF&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Whatever generates this error should be ignored, and the &lt;tt&gt;split&lt;/tt&gt; or &quot;&lt;tt&gt;setstripe --comp-add&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; command should be allowed to bring the file back into a consistent state.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
